investigation.title: Dataset for dose and time-dependent transcriptional response to ionizing radiation exposure.
investigation.description: One of the most likely risks astronauts on long duration space missions face is exposure to ionizing radiation associated with highly energetic and charged heavy (HZE) particles. Since access to medical expertise on such a mission is limited at best, early diagnosis and mitigation of such exposure is critical.

project.funding: Funding was provided by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) contract NX10AJ36G (BHF, ECR, JK, JWE, PKP, PS, RE and RSK); the National Institutes of Health (NIH) grants P20RR016481 (DL, ECR, RMF and SJW), 3P20RR016481-09S1 (ECR, RMF and SJW), and P20GM103436 (ECR and SJW).
